{"questionId":"9072719","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the atmospheric pressure. Give a suitable unit for your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{nRT}}}}{{\\text{A}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>nRT</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>A</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span> is constant <em><strong>OR</strong></em>&nbsp;190<em>p<span style=\"font-size:11.6667px;\"><sub>o</sub></span>&nbsp;</em>+&nbsp;190<em>p<sub>m</sub> =&nbsp;</em>208<em>p</em><sub>o</sub> − 208<em>p</em><sub>m</sub></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em>&nbsp; <em>p</em><sub>o</sub> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{398}{18}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>398</mn>\n    <mn>18</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> <em>p</em><sub>m</sub> ✔</p>\n<p>pressure due to mercury <em>p</em><sub>m</sub>&nbsp;= 0.035 × 1.36 × 10<sup>4</sup> × 9.81(= 4.67 × 10<sup>3</sup> Pa) ✔</p>\n<p>1.03 × 10<sup>5</sup> ✔</p>\n<p>Pa <em><strong>OR</strong></em> Nm<sup>-2</sup> <em><strong>OR</strong></em> kgm<sup>-1</sup>s<sup>-2</sup> ✔</p>\n<p><em>Do not award for a bald correct answer. Working must be shown to award MP3.</em></p>\n<p><em>Award MP4 for any correct unit of pressure (eg “mm of mercury / Hg”)</em>.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072719","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the atmospheric pressure. Give a suitable unit for your answer.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.1 – Thermal concepts","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}